c: 7
v: 95
t: "Then We replaced the unfavorable conditions and hardships by favourable circumstances until they advanced in power, importance and prosperity and proclaimed in ignorance that what has befallen them of misfortunes happened to their fathers before, \"and\", they added, \" it is only time that controls the wavering balance of fortune\". In consequence, We suddenly seized them and dressed them with ruin and We caught them unawares"